        "title": "Test Coverage Analysis — jobsquare",
        "content": "\n**Current state: zero tests.** No `tests/` directory, no `pytest`/`pytest-asyncio` in `requirements.txt`, no `conftest.py`. Every module below is fully untested. `httpx.AsyncClient` is already injectable in `fetchers.py` (explicitly designed for mocking — see its module docstring), so the fetchers are unit-testable without hitting the network via `httpx.MockTransport`.\n\nI'll organize by risk: pure-logic bugs first (cheapest to test, highest bang-for-buck), then I/O-boundary and integration gaps.\n\n---\n\n",
