      {
        "title": "Summary of gaps by priority",
        "content": "| Priority | Area | Why |\n|---|---|---|\n| **P0** | `filters.match`/`filter_jobs` | Core business logic, silent-wrong-answer risk (e.g. empty `include_keywords: []` matching everything, not nothing) |\n| **P0** | `store.py` diff/dedup + concurrent `next_seq` | Data-integrity bugs here corrupt `jobs.db` silently; memory already flags a prior parallel-worker collision incident |\n| **P0** | `notify.dispatch` per-notifier isolation | One misconfigured notifier (bad SMTP creds) must not silently kill SMS/Slack |\n| **P1** | `models.parse_posted_at` epoch/ISO branches | Feeds the recency filter directly; wrong parse = jobs silently dropped or kept |\n| **P1** | `agent._normalize_ats` | Silently corrupts every rendered PDF if a replacement rule leaks into `<style>`/attributes |\n| **P1** | `fetchers._request` retry/backoff | Every fetcher depends on it; untested retry-vs-fail-fast boundary (429/5xx vs 404) |\n| **P2** | Individual `parse_*` functions (20+) | High volume, each cheap to test, currently 0% covered; bugs here mean silently missing/malformed jobs per-ATS |\n| **P2** | `pipeline.run` end-to-end wiring | No integration test proves config→fetch→filter→dedup→notify actually connects |\n| **P3** | `agent.cmd_db_new` group-truncation logic | Subtle invariant (\"never split a first_seen group\") with no proof it holds |\n| **P3** | `fetch_all` per-source error isolation | One ATS 500ing shouldn't zero out the whole run — untested |\n\n**Setup gap:** add `pytest`, `pytest-asyncio`, and `respx` (or use `httpx.MockTransport` directly, no new dep needed) to `requirements.txt`/a `requirements-dev.txt`, plus a `pytest.ini` with `asyncio_mode = auto` — none of this exists yet, so even the skeletons above won't run without it.",
        "level": 3
      }
    ],
    "codeBlocks": [
      {
        "language": "python",
        "code": "# tests/test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"value,expected_year\", [\n    (\"\", None),\n    (None, None),\n    (\"not-a-date\", None),\n    (\"1643241332430\", 2022),          # ms epoch (13 digits)\n    (\"1643241332\", 2022),             # seconds epoch\n    (\"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\", 2024),   # trailing Z\n    (\"2024-01-15T10:00:00\", 2024),    # naive -> assumed UTC\n    (\"2024-01-15T10:00:00+05:30\", 2024),  # explicit offset preserved\n])\ndef test_parse_posted_at(value, expected_year):\n    dt = parse_posted_at(value)\n    if expected_year is None:\n        assert dt is None\n    else:\n        assert dt.year == expected_year\n        assert dt.tzinfo is not None\n\ndef test_job_key_and_content_hash_stable_across_title_edit():\n    j1 = Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"A\", url=\"u\")\n    j2 = Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"B\", url=\"u\")\n    assert j1.key == j2.key                    # key survives title change\n    assert j1.content_hash != j2.content_hash   # hash detects it\n\ndef test_job_to_row_drops_raw_adds_key_and_hash():\n    j = Job(source=\"lever\", company=\"x\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"t\", url=\"u\", raw={\"x\": 1})\n    row = j.to_row()\n    assert \"raw\" not in row\n    assert row[\"key\"] == j.key and row[\"content_hash\"] == j.content_hash"
      },
